# HRPayHub

HRPayHub is a web application for HR, payroll, and accounting solutions tailored for Nigerian businesses and UK pharmacies.

## Directory Structure
- `assets/`: CSS, JS, and image files.
  - `css/`: Stylesheets (styles.css, Bootstrap, Owl Carousel).
  - `js/`: JavaScript files (scripts.js, libraries).
  - `images/`: Images organized by page/purpose.
- `pages/`: HTML files for each page (index.html, about.html, etc.).
- `pages/partials/`: Reusable components (navbar.html, footer.html).

## Dependencies
- Bootstrap 5.3.2 (CDN: https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2)
- jQuery 3.6.0 (CDN: https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js)
- Owl Carousel 2.3.4 (CDN: https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/OwlCarousel2/2.3.4)

## Setup Instructions
1. Clone the repository: `git clone <repo-url>`
2. Serve the project using a local server:
   - Option 1: Use VS Code Live Server extension.
   - Option 2: Run `python -m http.server` in the project root.
3. Open `http://localhost:8000/pages/index.html` in a browser.

## Development Guidelines
- Use 2-space indentation for HTML/CSS/JS.
- Follow BEM naming for CSS classes (e.g., `.hero-section__title`).
- Add new pages in the `pages/` folder, reusing `navbar.html` and `footer.html` via includes.

## Handover Notes
- Video section: Placeholder images are used; actual video playback needs implementation.
- Form submission: Currently simulates submission; integrate with backend API (e.g., Node.js or PHP).
- Test mobile responsiveness for dropdown menus and carousel.

